The shortage of space in local schools has caused parents to call in backup. On Monday the EFF gathered at Laerskool Laeveld’s main gate for a peaceful protest to address various matters relating to children not being placed in their preferred schools.  ALSO READ: St Mark’s welcomes first grade ones at start of school year Laerskool Laeveld decided not to close the school for the day, because it had a contingency plan should the protest become violent. See Tuesday’s Lowvelder for the whole story.